President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. John Fernandez was nominated for Assistant Secretary of Commerce for Economic Development and Economic Development Administration Administrator. Anthony Marion Babauta was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Insular Areas, Department of the Interior. Joseph A. Main was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Mine Safety and Health, Department of Labor. Alexa E. Posny was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Special Education and Rehabilitative Services, Department of Education. Christopher P. Bertram was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Budget and Programs and Chief Financial Officer, Department of Transportation. Terry A. Yonkers was nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Installations and Environment, Department of the Air Force, Department of Defense. Kelvin James Cochran was nominated for U.S. Fire Administrator, Federal Emergency Management Agency, Department of Homeland Security. Joseph G. Pizarchik was nominated for Director, Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement, Department of the Interior. Daniel R. Elliott, III was nominated for Chairman, Surface Transportation Board. Patricia D. Cahill was nominated for Member of the Board of Directors, Corporation for Public Broadcasting. President Obama praised the nominees for their expertise and expressed gratitude for their decision to serve in his administration.